# Documentation

## Public docs (committed)

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `README.md` | Entry point: what, why, quick start, demo URL |
| `docs/architecture.md` | System design and data model |
| `docs/security.md` | Secrets, hooks, LLM boundaries |
| `docs/deployment.md` | Render and env vars |
| `docs/demo-guide.md` | Screen-share walkthrough |

## Local only (never commit)

- `SIGNALBRIEF_PLAN.md` — internal build plan and interview strategy

## When to update docs

In the **same commit** as the feature when you change:

- API routes or response shapes
- Environment variables → also update `.env.example`
- Risk rules, briefing schema, or seed narratives
- Deploy config (`render.yaml`) or npm scripts referenced in README

## Phase gate

Before marking a build phase complete:

1. README quick-start commands still work
2. New env vars appear in `.env.example` with placeholders
3. Architecture doc reflects actual file paths and services
4. Demo guide matches seeded account behavior

## Tone

Public docs are interviewer-safe: product and engineering focus only. No job-application strategy or private notes.
